 in your listing. So a well-crafted description can improve your click-through rate.</p>\";s:7:\"tooltip\";s:50:\"SEO analysis of your page&#039;s meta-description.\";s:3:\"fix\";s:338:\"<p>Write a meta-description for your page. Use your target keyword(s) (in a natural way) and write with human readers in mind. Summarize the content - describe the topics your article discusses.</p><p>The description should stimulate reader interest and get them to click on the article. Think of it as a mini-advert for your content.</p>\";s:6:\"status\";s:4:\"fail\";s:7:\"message\";s:118:\"The description of your page has 161 characters. Most search engines will truncate meta description to 160 characters.\";s:4:\"data\";s:161:\"As an Internet marketing agency we promote an integrated approach which makes our online marketing campaigns omnichannel. We will help your business grow online!\";}s:10:\"h1_heading\";a:10:{s:7:\"test_id\";s:10:\"h1_heading\";s:8:\"api_test\";b:1;s:5:\"title\";s:10:\"H1 Heading\";s:8:\"category\";s:5:\"basic\";s:8:\"priority\";s:4:\"high\";s:11:\"description\";s:1004:\"<p>The HTML H1 tag plays a very important role in SEO. It&#039;s the most dominant HTML header and is usually used for article titles. H2-H4 tags are used for less important headers (usually section headers). Together, the headers on a page should build a &quot;skeleton&quot; for the content.</p><p>Each page should only have a single HTML tag. It should include the most important keywords - search engines give special weight to keywords that appear in H1 tags, as they are usually the most visible text on the page.</p><p>The H1 tag should appear near the top of the page.</p><p>Text in the H1 tag usually acts as your content&#039;s headline - readers will usually scan the headline before they read the page&#039;s full text. If your headline sparks their interest, they are more likely to stick around and read the rest of your content. If it fails to grab them, they&#039;ll probably bounce.</p><p>H1 tags are the most important text on your page - both in terms of SEO and reader engagement.</p>\";s:7:\"tooltip\";s:41:\"SEO Analysis of the H1 Tags on your page.\";s:6:\"status\";s:2:\"ok\";s:7:\"message\";s:34:\"One H1 tag was found on your page.\";s:4:\"data\";a:1:{i:0;s:26:\"Digital marketing partners\";}}s:11:\"h2_headings\";a:10:{s:7:\"test_id\";s:11:\"h2_headings\";s:8:\"api_test\";b:1;s:5:\"title\";s:11:\"H2 Headings\";s:8:\"category\";s:5:\"basic\";s:8:\"priority\";s:6:\"medium\";s:11:\"description\";s:533:\"<p>While the H1 heading is usually used for post titles or headlines, H2 headings are used to break your text down into logical sections.</p><p>Well chosen H2 headings help search engines to understand the structure of your content. Keywords in H2 headings carry a larger weight than text in paragraphs.</p><p>H2 headings also help to improve reader retention. Often, people scan over web pages looking for sections that catch their eye. Headings can grab their attention and get them interested in reading the rest of your text.</p>\";s:7:\"tooltip\";s:45:\"SEO analysis of the H2 headings on your page.\";s:6:\"status\";s:2:\"ok\";s:7:\"message\";s:44:\"One or more H2 tags were found on your page.\";s:4:\"data\";a:7:{i:0;s:41:\"Our full-service digital marketing agency\";i:1;s:15:\"is here for you\";i:2;s:12:\"Our services\";i:3;s:30:\"Our clients’ success stories\";i:4;s:26:\"Where we excel over others\";i:5;s:10:\"Lets talk!\";i:6;s:25:\"Rampiq figure of the day:\";}}s:7:\"img_alt\";a:11:{s:7:\"test_id\";s:7:\"img_alt\";s:8:\"api_test\";b:1;s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Image ALT Attributes\";s:8:\"category\";s:5:\"basic\";s:8:\"priority\";s:6:\"medium\";s:11:\"description\";s:605:\"<p>Alt attributes are supposed to contain a short string of text that describes the contents of image tags. They&#039;re very useful for people who are browsing with images turned off, and they&#039;re vital for people who use screen readers.</p><p>In fact, they&#039;re a requirement